Courtesy #DStv403 JOHANNESBURG - Jacob Zuma is promising to be frank at the State Capture Inquiry on Monday. eNCA has been told the former president will answer all questions posed to him, in a bid to clear his name. He met the ANC's Secretary General Ace Magashule at Luthuli House. READ: Former president Zuma agrees to attend State Capture Inquiry Zuma has been heavily implicated in state capture but has questioned the independence of the Zondo Commission. The former president has undertaken to appear over five days in July. His attorney Lungisani Daniel Mantsha also accused the commission of trying to turn the public against the former president.